## Two categorical variables

::: question
What type of plot would you use to visualize the relationship between two categorical variables?
:::

. . .


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  mpg, 
  aes(x = class, fill = drv)
  ) +
  geom_bar(position = "fill") +
  labs(
    x = "Class",
    y = "Count",
    fill = "Drive type",
    title = "Drive type vs. class"
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](10-vizualize-model-relationships-I_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-3-1.png){width=480}
:::
:::


## One categorical, one numerical variable

::: question
What type of plot would you use to visualize the relationship between one numerical and one categorical variables?
:::

. . .


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  mpg, 
  aes(x = class, y = cty)
  ) +
  geom_boxplot() +
  labs(
    x = "Class",
    y = "City mileage (MPG)",
    title = "City mileage vs. class"
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](10-vizualize-model-relationships-I_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-4-1.png){width=480}
:::
:::


## Two numerical variables

::: question
What type of plot would you use to visualize the relationship between two numerical variables?
:::

. . .


::: {.cell output-location='column'}

```{.r .cell-code}
ggplot(
  mpg, 
  aes(x = cty, y = hwy)
  ) +
  geom_point() +
  labs(
    x = "City mileage (MPG)",
    y = "Highway mileage (MPG)",
    title = "Highway vs. city mileage"
  )
```

::: {.cell-output-display}
![](10-vizualize-model-relationships-I_files/figure-revealjs/unnamed-chunk-5-1.png){width=480}
:::
:::


